INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (70801, 'Public sentiment is everything, said Lincoln. With public sentiment, nothing can fail. Without it, nothing can succeed.', 11750, 0), (70802, 'Fair mindedness doesn''t require a lot of thought, it requires a lot of bravery.', 3620, 0), (70803, 'You can''t wear your brain out by overusing it.', 3620, 0), (70804, 'To have a flexible, open, clean mind, you have to do three things: exercise it, accept new ideas, clear out the clutter. Be willing to change your mind when it needs changing.', 3620, 0), (70805, 'The mid-19th century was noted for a partisan, rather than a consensus press, but this partisanship was able to turn out voters consistently.', 11750, 0), (70806, 'You can''t have a great life unless you move two things: your body AND your mind. Keep them both exercised by taking them places they''ve never before been.', 3620, 0), (70807, 'I will never be a loser. Never. Because I will never stop trying to be better.', 3620, 0), (70808, 'In order to be a success, you must think like success. Get up and move! You got to make things happen.', 3145, 0), (70809, 'There are two levers for moving man -- interest and fear.', 1702, 0), (70810, 'Sometimes great achievements arrive much later than we expect, but they arrive, and they are great.', 15089, 0), (70811, 'Weight gains aren''t failures – they''re learning curves.', 15090, 0), (70812, 'The mightiest flame of fire lies in positive mindset.', 2878, 0), (70813, 'Never settle up for something that is lesser than what you expected.', 5149, 0), (70814, 'Greatness can be contagious, but first there must be contact.', 5028, 0), (70815, 'Imagination can take you to any place of interest.', 2878, 0), (70816, 'The human spirit holds remarkable strength, in times of adversity and pain, some stand taller after they''ve fallen proving that you can''t measure a want, a desire or a dream on the logic of physical reality.', 3305, 0), (70817, 'Start anywhere, with whatever is in front of you. The key is to begin - and to trust that as long as you’re putting one foot in front of the other, eventually you''ll get to where you need to, or at the very least, much farther than you had initially imagined.', 15091, 0), (70818, 'Life is too short to spend even one day in misery.-RVM', 5635, 0), (70819, 'In the infancy of society every author is necessarily a poet, because language itself is poetry. – Owen Barfield', 11752, 0), (70820, 'Shine thy light.', 2878, 0), (70821, 'Begin to study. You can master any field of choice.', 2878, 0), (70822, 'Never forget the life experiences', 15092, 0), (70823, 'Be sacred soul.', 2878, 0), (70824, 'A moment spent in Sorrow or a moment spent in Pain is a waste of a Great Treasure that you will never get again. -RVM', 5635, 0), (70825, 'Mento mori—remember death! These are important words. If we kept in mind that we will soon inevitably die, our lives would be completely different. If a person knows that he will die in a half hour, he certainly will not bother doing trivial, stupid, or, especially, bad things during this half hour. Perhaps you have half a century before you die—what makes this any different from a half hour?', 93, 0), (70826, 'Motivation is a state of mind, just like discouragement.', 5845, 0), (70827, 'Don’t just GO through life, GROW through it. For Life comes to you only once, never to return! Climb the Ladder of Life, step by step.-RVM', 5635, 0), (70828, 'Life Begins at the end of your comfort zone.', 15093, 0), (70829, 'What happens to us are tiny matters compare to our motivation to live through every tribulations.', 2878, 0), (70830, 'Inspiration is that Power that makes you Seek and reach the Peak.-RVM', 5635, 0), (70831, 'If you want something bad enough, then do something about it!', 15094, 0), (70832, 'in our life many moments which can only be set-forth as best and described as perfect, only these are the moments that you wish were rooted in heart, in mind, in time, and effectively ignore all kind of cruelty and sadness this world has to offer. Unfortunately we can not prevent it from our life, because fortunate or unfortunate finally we’re all going to have to live it. And as perfect as a moment is, don’t be shocked, don''t be scared to let it go and confront the world with your true-cent, with your positive impact and move forward in this unstable/unexpected journey of life. As appealing it is to have that one moment where life made sense and beautiful frozen in time, remember that there are many more ‘perfect’ moments fabricated on your way waiting for you…to sweep over the challenges of life to make each moment worth it..', 15095, 0), (70833, 'The mightiest flame of fire lies positive mindset.', 2878, 0), (70834, 'The engine that drives all your activities is hope. What you hope in shapes you.', 3369, 0), (70835, 'I celebrate myself, I paint and dance and sing myself, and what I assume you will assume, for every atom as of me as good belongs to dreamy You. I am a song. I am a poem. I am the soil and a gem. I am a stargate and a voyage. I am the ocean and your soul.', 15096, 0), (70836, 'Growth is ugly, it''s hideous, it''s all the things we don''t like but my god, once you walk through the fire of confusion you will feel burning passion within your flame.', 3305, 0), (70837, 'Take the time out to have a look at yourself, it might help you to appreciate yourself better.', 15079, 0), (70838, 'Everything good starts with caring.', 15079, 0), (70839, 'When you love your work, it works better.', 15079, 0), (70840, 'Destiny reveals itself only when there is truth and action.', 2678, 0), (70841, 'Motivation 1.0 presumed that humans were biological creatures, struggling to obtain our basic needs for food, security and sex.Motivation 2.0 presumed that humans also responded to rewards and punishments. That worked fine for routine tasks but incompatible with how we organize what we do, how we think about what we do, and howwe do what we do.